	(509,51,'instructions_3_step','Divide the dough into 1 to 1½ tablespoon sized balls and drop onto prepared baking sheets with a couple inches between them.'),
	(510,51,'_instructions_3_step','field_5341debeae3dd'),
	(511,51,'instructions_4_step','Bake for 8-10 minutes, or until golden brown. Cool for 2 minutes before removing to wire racks or paper towels to cool completely.'),
	(512,51,'_instructions_4_step','field_5341debeae3dd'),
	(513,51,'instructions','5'),
	(514,51,'_instructions','field_5341de74ae3dc'),
	(515,51,'alternatives','<em><strong>Alternatives:</strong> Try wrapping dough in plastic wrap and refrigerating for 24 hours, but no more than 72 hours, after mixing. Then let dough sit at room temperature just until soft enough to scoop.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Also, try replacing half the chocolate chips with candy-coated chocolate pieces, white chocolate pieces, or peanut butter pieces.</em>'),
	(516,51,'_alternatives','field_5341df4cae3de'),
	(517,51,'tips','<em><strong>Tip:</strong> If you keep the butter in the refrigerator or freezer and don\'t want to wait for it to come to room temperature, use a cheese grater to shred the sticks into your mixing bowl before you start. Prepare the dry ingredients in another bowl while you wait and after 5-10 minutes the butter should be soft enough to work with.</em>'),
